PN,41506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1779466274
OL,3,CReform UK council to introduce Lord's
OL,4,CPrayer and national anthem at meetings
OL,6,FOther changes approved included
OL,7,Fcutting the time allowed for
OL,8,Fopposition party leaders to respond to
OL,9,Fthe report by the council leader, with
OL,10,Fa minimum limit of two minutes each.
OL,12,FIt will see the leader of the
OL,13,Fopposition group be able to speak up
OL,14,Fto five minutes, with the other
OL,15,Fopposition leaders time dependent on
OL,16,Ftheir group's size, losing a minute
OL,17,Ffrom the maximum time allowed.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1779466274
OL,3,CReform UK council to introduce Lord's
OL,4,CPrayer and national anthem at meetings
OL,6,FOn reducing response times, Mr Hespe
OL,7,Fsaid: "There is no intention to reduce
OL,8,Fdemocracy or scrutiny but to reduce
OL,9,Fverbosity.
OL,11,F"Nobody wants to hear repetitive
OL,12,Fmonotonous waffle."
OL,14,FHe added that the current time
OL,15,Fallocated is 22 minutes which is
OL,16,Fhigher than the 17 minutes allowed a
OL,17,Fyear ago.
OL,19,F"Our proposal would reduce it back
OL,20,Fdown to 17 minutes response to the
OL,21,Fleader's speech of just 10 minutes."
OL,26,@oD@GOUsD@AOUtD@SO]{D@AOU}D@dO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
